                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" class="maintitle"> PGCE - Money matters for 2006 </td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <p><strong>Fees</strong><br>
                    <br>
                    Leeds Trinity &amp; All Saints are in the process of determining the fees policy for 2006 and will keep applicants informed of fee levels when these have been set. As with other ITT providers, our fee and bursary provision is subject to the approval of our access agreement by the Office of Fair Access (OFFA).<br>
                    <br>
                    Grants From September 2006, students in England will be eligible for a non-means tested grant of &pound;1,200 and to apply for an additional means-tested grant of &pound;1,500. In Wales the Welsh Assembly Government is currently reviewing the incentives package for 2006-7 and an announcement on this will be made shortly. Visit the <a href="http://www.dfes.gov.uk/studentsupport/students/index.shtml">DfES student support website</a> for full details of funding available for home students and how you can apply . </p>
                    <p>Separate arrangements have been put in place for EU students. Please check the <a href="http://www.dfes.gov.uk/studentsupport/eustudents/index.shtml">DfES EU website</a> for full details of funding available to students from the EU . </p>
<p>In addition, eligible postgraduate trainee teachers are entitled to a tax-free bursary while they train, the value of which will depend on where you train, the subject you are training to teach, and when you start your course. </p>
<p><strong>Bursaries&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; </p>
<p>From September 2006: </p>
<p>&pound;9,000 (&pound;225 a week) for trainees in secondary mathematics; science; English (including drama); ICT ; D&amp;T ; modern languages; RE ; music </p>
<p>&pound;6,000 (&pound;150 a week) for trainees in all other subjects </p>
<p>The Welsh Assembly Government is currently reviewing the incentives available in Wales and will make an announcement about bursaries for the academic year 2006/07 as soon as possible </p>
<p>For more information please visit the Course Funding page on the Training and Development Agency website or <a href="http://www.tda.gov.uk/home/recruit/thetrainingprocess/coursefunding.aspx#anchor4">click this link to be redirected to their site. </a> </p><p><strong>Golden hellos </strong></p>
<p>If you complete a postgraduate ITT and take up an NQT position in a&nbsp; <a href="/Home/Recruit/lifeasateacher/achoiceofschools.aspx">maintained school </a> or non-maintained special school in England, you may be eligible to receive a one-off, taxable 'golden hello' payment of between &pound;2,500 and &pound;5,000 at the start of your second year of teaching, after successfully completing&nbsp; <a href="/Home/Recruit/becomingateacher/inductionyear.aspx">your induction period </a>. </p>
<p>For more information please visit the Money Matters page on the Training and Development Agency website or <a href="http://www.tda.gov.uk/home/recruit/becomingateacher/moneymatters.aspx">click this link to be redirected to their site. </a> </p><p><strong>When to apply </strong></p>
<p>You should apply for a PGCE as early as you can. If you apply late in the cycle, you may not have time to produce all your clearance documents, and this can have a&nbsp;negative effect on your training salary. </p>
<p>If you are commencing a PGCE, you must contact your local education authority to let them know. To find out contact details for your LEA click here </p>
<p><strong>Further information </strong></p>
<p>If you have any queries about finance and funding, email us at <a href="mailto:studentfinance@leedstrinity.ac.uk">studentfinance@leedstrinity.ac.uk</a> or call 0113 283 7173. </p>
<p><br>
